The vulnerability arises from inadequate bounds tracking for 32-bit arithmetic and bitwise operations in kernel code. Specifically, bitwise operations are performed on registers without proper bounds checking, potentially leading to incorrect assumptions about valid value ranges. The solution involves explicitly marking the destination register's value as known when both the source and destination registers have known values.

